scanty /ˈskæntɪ/

(scantier,scantiest) 

1. ADJ You describe something as scanty when there is less of it than you think there should be. 缺乏的; 不足的 

例： So far, what scanty evidence we have points to two suspects. 目前，我们指向两名嫌犯的证据太少。 

2. ADJ If someone is wearing scanty clothing, he or she is wearing clothes which are sexually revealing. (衣着)暴露的 [ADV -ed/adj] 

例： ...a model in scanty clothing. ...一个衣着暴露的模特。 

3. scantily ADV 

例： ...a troupe of scantily-clad dancers. ...一团穿戴暴露的舞蹈演员。

